While a `window.showInformationMessage()` works fine in a mocha `before()` block (as also showcased [here](https://code.visualstudio.com/api/working-with-extensions/testing-extension#debugging-the-tests) in the testing extensions guide), it doesn't have any effect when placed in a `test()` block and in debugging mode. Things like `window.createTerminal("yo");` also don't work, e.g. a new terminal is _not_ spawned when we step over this line. See this video:
https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/68849aa6-07af-4a83-97de-0baa241629b8
Our `.vscode-test.mjs` file:
```mjs
import { defineConfig } from "@vscode/test-cli";

export default defineConfig({
  files: "out/test/**/*.test.js",
  version: "stable",
  workspaceFolder: "tests/fixtures",
});

```
> [!tip]
> See [my comment here](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-extension-test-runner/issues/58#issuecomment-2563748165) for a better reproducible example.
The sample test file:
```ts
import * as assert from "assert";
import * as vscode from "vscode";
import { window } from "vscode";
// import * as note from "../src/extension";
import { before } from "mocha";

suite("General Tests", () => {
  before(() => {
    window.showInformationMessage("Start all tests.");
  });

  test("Sample test", async () => {
    assert.strictEqual(-1, [1, 2, 3].indexOf(5));
    assert.strictEqual(-1, [1, 2, 3].indexOf(0));

    const terminal = window.createTerminal("yo");
    terminal.show();
    terminal.sendText("ls");

    window.showInformationMessage("Sample test passed.");
  });
});

```
- Note that nothing changes when I `await` the `createTerminal()`. Then, I do see the terminal variable in the "Variables" section of the "Run and Debug" view in my host window. However, the terminal is not actually shown in the extension VSCode window.
- After having stopped for the break point, when I then continue the execution, I see how the extension window shows the final information message. But this is only for a few milliseconds before the VSCode window closes since the test execution is finished.
- For more context of the code, see also https://github.com/Manim-Notebook/manim-notebook/pull/106 and in particular commit [3ef24fecb2a88a](https://github.com/Manim-Notebook/manim-notebook/pull/106/commits/3ef24fecb2a88a558264913d193d57c2782496b8)
- Update: If you add an `await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));` after the `terminal.sendText("ls")` and then step over it, the terminal is only created once we step over the additional waiting promise:
```ts
const terminal = await window.createTerminal("yo");
terminal.show();
terminal.sendText("ls");
await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
```
That is to say that the `await` does not work here in the test.

